desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:4:- Tauri v2 desktop application with Rust backend and web frontend
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:5:- Rust commands are defined in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs` using `#[tauri::command]` macro
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:6:- Plugins are registered in the `tauri::Builder` chain in `run()`
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:7:- Capabilities (permissions) are configured in `src-tauri/capabilities/default.json`
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:10:- `tauri-plugin-dialog`: Native file/folder dialogs (`DialogExt`)
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:11:- `tauri-plugin-store`: Key-value persistence (`StoreExt`, stored in `app.json`)
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:12:- `tauri-plugin-opener`: Default opener plugin
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:14:## Tauri Commands
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:15:- Commands use `tauri::AppHandle` for accessing plugins
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:29:- Tauri commands consistently use `Result<T, String>` for error handling
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:40:- When a Tauri command shells out to `gh`, extract pure helper functions for JSON parsing and stderr-to-user-error mapping so unit tests do not depend on a live GitHub CLI session
desktop_app/CLAUDE.md:42:- Keep the `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block at the end of `src-tauri/src/lib.rs` to satisfy clippy's `items_after_test_module` lint
